## Key Points

Traffic vs. Revenue: Publishers and affiliates are getting crushed by AIO, but SaaS and e-commerce brands are seeing flat or growing revenue. AI traffic converts at a much higher rate than traditional organic clicks.

User Behavior in AIO: About 85% of users click "load more" on AI Overviews, but they mostly just skim the top third. Getting cited early in the response is critical.

The "Verification" Loop: Users don't just blindly trust AI. They use platforms like Reddit, YouTube, G2, and Trustpilot to verify AI answers. Your off-site reputation and community presence are now direct ranking factors for AI.

Google vs. ChatGPT: In consolidated markets (like CRM software), the winners on Google are the same on ChatGPT. In fragmented markets (like e-commerce), the winners are often completely different. You have to monitor both.

Using AI for Marketing: Stop using AI just to write generic blog posts. Use it to analyze sales call transcripts (via tools like Gong or Humata) to find real customer pain points. Also, use "vibe coding" tools (like v0 or Cursor) to quickly build interactive calculators and widgets that boost conversions.